// TEST: counterexample-fn "want_big"
// TEST: counterexample-blame callee
// TEST: counterexample-vow-id 0
// TEST: replay skipped
//
// Counterexample-replay skip fixture (#335). `want_big` takes a `String`, which
// is outside the v1 reconstruction scope (scalars + bounded Vec), so harness
// generation cannot build a concrete input. `s.len()` is bounded by the string
// model and can never equal 999, violating `ensures: result == 999` (Callee
// blame). With `--replay-cex` both compilers report replay "skipped" with a
// reason naming the unsupported parameter type.
module ReplaySkipString

fn want_big(s: String) -> i64 vow {
  ensures: result == 999
} {
  s.len()
}
